quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  26,123,Ad denied the messengers
  26,124,"when their brother Hud said unto them, “Will you not be reverent"
  26,125,Truly I am a trustworthy messenger unto you
  26,126,So reverence God and obey me
  26,127,And I ask not of you any reward for it; my reward lies only with the Lord of the worlds
  26,128,Do you frivolously build on every high place a sign
  26,129,"And do you occupy castles, that haply you may ever abide"
  26,130,"And when you strike, do you strike as tyrants"
  26,131,So reverence God and obey me
  26,132,And reverence Him who has succored you with what you know
  26,133,succored you with cattle and children
  26,134,and gardens and springs
  26,135,Truly I fear for you the punishment of a tremendous day!”
  26,136,"They said, “It is the same to us whether you exhort us or whether you are not among those who exhort"
  26,137,This is naught but the ethos of those of old
  26,138,and we shall not be punished.”
  26,139,"So they denied him, and We destroyed them. Truly in that is a sign, but most of them are not believers"
  26,140,"And truly thy Lord is, indeed, the Mighty, the Merciful"